{"uid": "database-connections", "title": "4 - Database Connection Pools", "tags": ["workshop", "database", "bug"], "timezone": "browser", "schemaVersion": 16, "version": 0, "refresh": "5s", "panels": [{"id": 10, "gridPos": {"h": 10, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 0}, "type": "text", "title": "", "options": {"mode": "html", "content": "<div style='font-family:Inter,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;padding:12px 16px;color:#d8d9da;display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:24px'><div><p style='font-size:0.75rem;font-weight:600;color:#ff9830;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.1em;margin:0 0 8px 0'>How to Trigger</p><div style='background:#1a1b1f;border:1px solid #2c3235;border-radius:6px;padding:10px 16px;font-family:monospace;font-size:0.85rem;color:#73bf69'>$ oha -z 30s -c 50 http://localhost/api/orders/20000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001</div><p style='font-size:0.75rem;font-weight:600;color:#ff9830;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.1em;margin:16px 0 4px 0'>Location</p><p style='font-size:0.83rem;color:#aaa;margin:0;font-family:monospace'>configuration/dev.yaml \u2014 pool_max_connections: 5</p></div><div><p style='font-size:0.75rem;font-weight:600;color:#ff9830;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.1em;margin:0 0 8px 0'>What's Happening</p><p style='font-size:0.83rem;color:#aaa;margin:0 0 10px 0'>Service C's Postgres pool allows only 5 concurrent connections. Service B's N+1 pattern drives 50 requests per order into Service C. Under even modest load the pool exhausts, new requests queue, and then fail with timeout errors.</p><p style='font-size:0.7rem;font-weight:600;color:#8e8e8e;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.08em;margin:0 0 4px 0'>How to identify</p><ul style='font-size:0.83rem;color:#aaa;margin:0 0 10px 0;padding-left:16px'><li>Postgres active connections pin at 5 (the pool max) \u2014 the direct signal</li><li>Service C error rate climbs as requests fail waiting for a free connection</li><li>Service C p99 latency spikes before errors appear (requests queuing)</li></ul><p style='font-size:0.7rem;font-weight:600;color:#8e8e8e;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.08em;margin:0 0 4px 0'>The Fix</p><p style='font-size:0.83rem;color:#aaa;margin:0'>Increase <code style='background:#1a1b1f;padding:1px 4px;border-radius:3px'>pool_max_connections</code> to 20\u201350; or fix Service B's N+1 bug to reduce request fan-out into Service C.</p></div></div>"}}, {"id": 1, "gridPos": {"h": 9, "w": 12, "x": 0, "y": 10}, "type": "timeseries", "title": "Service C - Request Rate vs Errors", "description": "When pool is exhausted, error rate approaches total rate", "targets": [{"expr": "sum(rate(traces_spanmetrics_calls_total{span_kind=\"SPAN_KIND_SERVER\",service=\"service-c-products\"}[1m]))", "legendFormat": "Total requests", "refId": "A"}, {"expr": "sum(rate(traces_spanmetrics_calls_total{span_kind=\"SPAN_KIND_SERVER\",service=\"service-c-products\",status_code=\"STATUS_CODE_ERROR\"}[1m]))", "legendFormat": "Errors (pool exhausted)", "refId": "B"}], "fieldConfig": {"defaults": {"custom": {"drawStyle": "line", "fillOpacity": 30, "lineWidth": 2}, "unit": "reqps"}, "overrides": [{"matcher": {"id": "byName", "options": "Errors (pool exhausted)"}, "properties": [{"id": "color", "value": {"mode": "fixed", "fixedColor": "red"}}]}]}}, {"id": 2, "gridPos": {"h": 9, "w": 12, "x": 12, "y": 10}, "type": "timeseries", "title": "Service C - p99 Latency", "description": "Latency spikes when connections are queued waiting for pool", "targets": [{"expr": "histogram_quantile(0.99, sum by (le) (rate(traces_spanmetrics_latency_bucket{span_kind=\"SPAN_KIND_SERVER\",service=\"service-c-products\"}[1m])))", "legendFormat": "p99 latency", "refId": "A"}, {"expr": "histogram_quantile(0.50, sum by (le) (rate(traces_spanmetrics_latency_bucket{span_kind=\"SPAN_KIND_SERVER\",service=\"service-c-products\"}[1m])))", "legendFormat": "p50 latency", "refId": "B"}], "fieldConfig": {"defaults": {"custom": {"drawStyle": "line", "fillOpacity": 10}, "unit": "ms"}}}, {"id": 5, "gridPos": {"h": 8, "w": 12, "x": 0, "y": 19}, "type": "timeseries", "title": "Postgres - Active Connections by State", "description": "From pg_stat_activity. When 'active' pins at 5 (the pool max), the pool is exhausted and new requests fail.", "targets": [{"expr": "sum(pg_stat_activity_count{state=\"active\"})", "legendFormat": "Active", "refId": "A"}, {"expr": "sum(pg_stat_activity_count{state=\"idle\"})", "legendFormat": "Idle", "refId": "B"}], "fieldConfig": {"defaults": {"custom": {"drawStyle": "line", "fillOpacity": 20, "lineWidth": 2}, "unit": "short", "min": 0}, "overrides": [{"matcher": {"id": "byName", "options": "Active"}, "properties": [{"id": "color", "value": {"mode": "fixed", "fixedColor": "orange"}}]}, {"matcher": {"id": "byName", "options": "Idle"}, "properties": [{"id": "color", "value": {"mode": "fixed", "fixedColor": "green"}}]}]}}, {"id": 6, "gridPos": {"h": 8, "w": 12, "x": 12, "y": 19}, "type": "timeseries", "title": "Redis - Connected Clients & Memory", "description": "From redis_exporter. Connected clients spike during the cache miss thundering herd.", "targets": [{"expr": "redis_connected_clients", "legendFormat": "Connected clients", "refId": "A"}, {"expr": "redis_blocked_clients", "legendFormat": "Blocked clients", "refId": "B"}], "fieldConfig": {"defaults": {"custom": {"drawStyle": "line", "fillOpacity": 10, "lineWidth": 2}, "unit": "short", "min": 0}}}, {"id": 3, "gridPos": {"h": 8, "w": 12, "x": 0, "y": 27}, "type": "timeseries", "title": "All Services - Error Rates", "targets": [{"expr": "sum by (service) (rate(traces_spanmetrics_calls_total{span_kind=\"SPAN_KIND_SERVER\",status_code=\"STATUS_CODE_ERROR\"}[1m]))", "legendFormat": "{{service}}", "refId": "A"}], "fieldConfig": {"defaults": {"custom": {"drawStyle": "line", "fillOpacity": 10}, "unit": "reqps"}}}, {"id": 7, "gridPos": {"h": 8, "w": 12, "x": 12, "y": 27}, "type": "timeseries", "title": "Postgres - Row Fetch Rate", "description": "From pg_stat_database. Rate of rows fetched from Postgres. Under the N+1 bug each order drives ~50 DB queries \u2014 watch this climb proportionally with Service B request rate.", "targets": [{"expr": "rate(pg_stat_database_tup_fetched{datname=\"postgres\"}[1m])", "legendFormat": "Rows fetched/sec", "refId": "A"}, {"expr": "rate(pg_stat_database_tup_returned{datname=\"postgres\"}[1m])", "legendFormat": "Rows returned/sec (seq scans)", "refId": "B"}], "fieldConfig": {"defaults": {"custom": {"drawStyle": "line", "fillOpacity": 10, "lineWidth": 2}, "unit": "ops"}}}, {"id": 20, "gridPos": {"h": 3, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 35}, "type": "text", "title": "", "options": {"mode": "html", "content": "<div style='font-family:Inter,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;padding:8px 16px;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:flex-end;height:100%'><a href='/d/cpu-profiling' style='display:inline-block;padding:8px 24px;background:#ff9830;color:#111;border-radius:6px;font-weight:600;font-size:0.9rem;text-decoration:none'>\u2192 Next: 5 - CPU Profiling</a></div>"}}], "time": {"from": "now-2m", "to": "now"}}